AN exhibition for building interior items is slated for next week, running from March 10 to 13 at the Oshwal Centre in Nairobi.The Ideal Interiors' expo will offer a platform for industry players to showcase new trends in furniture, homewares, wall decoration, kitchens, bathrooms and products such as lighting, flooring, furnishings, textiles and table tops.Organisers said the expo will offer suppliers of home, office and hotel interiors a great opportunity to also sell products directly to thousands of targeted shoppers."Our overall aim is to increase awareness and desire to create inspiring and unique living spaces and environments," the organisers said in a statement.The expo has been organised by Ideal Interiors with the support of National Construction Authority, Interior Designers Association of Kenya and Kenya Vision 2030.